item.title: Jack Newsome - Give It Back
item.description:
When I walk down your apartment stairs
I think I left my jacket there
Could you give it back?
And while you’re at it
I might have left my heart there, too
Since it’s no use to you, I just thought I’d ask
Could you give that back, too?

[Chorus]
I don’t have the right to
Miss you as bad as I do
Lately, it’s all I do
I know you’ve still got something of mine
So give it back

[Verse 2]
All my spare keys on the windowsill
Toothbrush in the bathroom still
Going nowhere fast, just smiling less
Can you check in your kitchen shelf?
I might have left my sense of self
And I need that bad
Could you give that back, too?

[Chorus]
I don’t have the right to
Miss you as bad as I do
But, lately, it’s all I do
Because you still have something of mine
Give it back
Oh, give it back

[Outro]
Don’t wanna open back up
Any wounds, any cuts
But something’s missing inside
And I know I hurt you
So, really, who am I to
Take anymore from you?
But I think you still have something that’s mine
So give it back
